.TH SHOREWALL-NFT 8 "2026-04-12" "shorewall-nft 1.4.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft \- nftables-native firewall compiler with Shorewall-compatible configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shorewall\-nft
.I COMMAND
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ DIRECTORY ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shorewall\-nft
is a Python implementation of the Shorewall firewall compiler that
emits native nftables rulesets instead of iptables. It is a drop\-in
replacement for Shorewall that reads the same configuration files
and produces semantically equivalent firewall behavior on modern
Linux kernels.

Configuration files live under \fI/etc/shorewall\fR (v4),
\fI/etc/shorewall6\fR (v6), or \fI/etc/shorewall46\fR (merged
dual\-stack, produced by \fBshorewall\-nft merge\-config\fR). The
merged directory takes precedence when all three are present.

.SH LIFECYCLE COMMANDS
.TP
.B start \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Compile and apply the firewall ruleset.
.TP
.B stop \fR[\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Remove all rules from the inet shorewall table.
.TP
.B restart \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Recompile and atomically replace the loaded ruleset.
.TP
.B reload \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Alias for restart (nft does atomic replace natively).
.TP
.B status \fR[\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Show firewall status, chain/rule count, and config hash drift warning
if the on-disk config differs from the loaded ruleset.
.TP
.B clear \fR[\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Remove all rules and install accept-all policies.
.TP
.B save \fR[\fIFILENAME\fR] [\fB\-C\fR] [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Dump the current ruleset to file (\fB\-C\fR includes counter values).
.TP
.B restore \fIFILENAME\fR [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Load a saved ruleset from file.
.TP
.B check \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-\-skip\-caps\fR]
Compile without applying. Validates config and kernel capabilities.
.TP
.B compile \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-o\fR \fIFILE\fR]
Compile the config to an nft script, print to stdout or \fB\-o\fR file.

.SH INSPECTION COMMANDS
.TP
.B show \fR[\fIWHAT\fR] [\fB\-x\fR] [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Show firewall info. \fIWHAT\fR: \fBzones\fR, \fBpolicies\fR,
\fBconfig\fR, \fBconnections\fR. \fB\-x\fR shows exact counter values.
.TP
.B counters \fR[\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
List all named counter values (packets and bytes) for the loaded ruleset.
.TP
.B reset \fR[\fICHAINS\fR] [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Reset packet/byte counters.
.TP
.B capabilities \fR[\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR]
Probe and report nftables capabilities of the running kernel.
.TP
.B explain\-nft\-features \fR[\fB\-\-probe\fR] [\fB\-\-category\fR \fICATEGORY\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR]
Show the nft feature catalog with syntax examples. \fB\-\-probe\fR tests
kernel availability. \fB\-\-category\fR filters by name (e.g. Sets, NAT, IPv6).

.SH DYNAMIC BLACKLIST
.TP
.B drop \fIADDRESSES\fR [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Dynamically drop all traffic from the given addresses.
.TP
.B reject \fIADDRESSES\fR [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Dynamically reject traffic from the given addresses (sends TCP RST or
ICMP unreachable).
.TP
.B blacklist \fIADDRESS\fR [\fB\-t\fR \fITIMEOUT\fR] [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Add address to the dynamic blacklist. \fB\-t\fR accepts duration
strings: \fB1h\fR, \fB30m\fR, \fB1d\fR.
.TP
.B allow \fIADDRESSES\fR [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Remove addresses from the dynamic blacklist.

.SH NFT-NATIVE EXTENSIONS
.TP
.B debug \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR] [\fB\-\-trace\fR \fIFILTER\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-restore\fR]
Temporarily load a debug\-annotated ruleset with per\-rule named
counters and source\-location comments. Ctrl+C restores the original
ruleset. \fB\-\-trace\fR installs a \fBmeta nftrace set 1\fR rule
(e.g. \fB'ip saddr 192.168.1.1'\fR) removed on exit.
.TP
.B trace \fR[\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Run \fBnft monitor trace\fR. Packets matched by a rule with
\fBmeta nftrace set 1\fR produce trace events.
.TP
.B verify \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] \fB\-\-iptables\fR \fIDUMP\fR
Semantic comparison (triangle verifier) between the compiled nft output
and an \fBiptables\-save\fR baseline.
.TP
.B simulate \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] \fB\-\-iptables\fR \fIDUMP\fR [\fB\-\-target\fR \fIIP\fR] [\fB\-n\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB\-\-seed\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB\-j\fR \fIN\fR]
Packet\-level verification in 3 network namespaces using Scapy.
.TP
.B migrate \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-\-iptables\fR \fIDUMP\fR] [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
Verify migration readiness from Shorewall. \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR runs
\fBnft \-c\fR syntax check only without loading rules.
.TP
.B lookup \fIIP\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR]
Query all configured plugins for metadata about an IP address.
.TP
.B enrich \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
Rewrite \fB?COMMENT\fR blocks in\-place with plugin annotations
(creates \fI.bak\fR backup by default).
.TP
.B load\-sets \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR] [\fB\-\-geoip\-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR]
Load external sets (GeoIP prefix files, ipset exports) into nft after
\fBstart\fR.
.TP
.B merge\-config \fIV4\fR [\fIV6\fR] [\fB\-o\fR \fIOUT\fR] [\fB\-\-guided\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-plugins\fR]
Merge \fI/etc/shorewall\fR and \fI/etc/shorewall6\fR into a unified
\fI/etc/shorewall46\fR directory. \fB\-\-guided\fR asks interactively
on each naming collision.
.TP
.B plugins list
Show loaded plugins with their names, versions, and priorities.

.SH GENERATORS
.TP
.B generate\-systemd \fR[\fB\-\-netns\fR] [\fB\-o\fR \fIDIR\fR]
Print a systemd service unit to stdout. \fB\-\-netns\fR produces a
templated unit (\fBshorewall\-nft@.service\fR) for per\-netns instances.
.TP
.B generate\-sysctl \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
Print a sysctl configuration script derived from interface options.
.TP
.B generate\-tc \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
Print \fBtc\fR commands to set up traffic control classes.
.TP
.B generate\-set\-loader \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
Print a shell script that loads external sets (GeoIP, ipset dumps)
into nft at startup.

.SH CONFIG DIRECTORY OVERRIDE FLAGS
All commands that take a \fIDIRECTORY\fR also accept these mutually
exclusive mode overrides:
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config\-dir " \fIDIR\fR"
Explicit merged config directory (overrides \fI/etc/shorewall46\fR default).
.TP
.BI \-\-config\-dir4 " DIR"
Explicit IPv4-only config directory.
.TP
.BI \-\-config6\-dir " DIR"
Explicit IPv6-only config directory (combine with \fB\-\-config\-dir4\fR for
explicit dual mode).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-auto\-v4
Disable auto\-detection of a v4 sibling directory (v6\-only mode).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-auto\-v6
Disable auto\-detection of a v6 sibling directory (v4\-only mode).

The six supported config-dir modes are:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Default: \fBshorewall\-nft start\fR — uses \fI/etc/shorewall46\fR if present, else \fI/etc/shorewall\fR
.IP \(bu 2
Merged explicit: \fBshorewall\-nft start \-c /srv/merged\fR
.IP \(bu 2
Dual auto\-sibling: \fBshorewall\-nft start /srv/v4\fR — detects /srv/v6 automatically
.IP \(bu 2
Dual explicit: \fBshorewall\-nft start \-\-config\-dir4 /srv/v4 \-\-config6\-dir /srv/v6\fR
.IP \(bu 2
v4\-only: \fBshorewall\-nft start \-\-config\-dir4 /srv/v4 \-\-no\-auto\-v6\fR
.IP \(bu 2
v6\-only: \fBshorewall\-nft start \-\-config6\-dir /srv/v6 \-\-no\-auto\-v4\fR
.RE

.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-netns " \fINAMESPACE\fR"
Target a Linux network namespace. Requires
\fB/usr/local/bin/run\-netns\fR (installed by \fBinstall\-test\-tooling.sh\fR
or the \fBshorewall\-nft\-tests\fR package).
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help for the command and exit.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall/
Legacy IPv4 Shorewall config directory.
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall6/
Legacy IPv6 Shorewall config directory.
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall46/
Merged dual\-stack config directory (takes precedence when present).
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall/plugins.conf
Plugin registry (TOML format).
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall/plugins/*.toml
Per\-plugin configuration files.
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall/dnsnames
Optional per-hostname TTL/size overrides for DNS-driven nft sets.
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall/dnsnames.compiled
Written by \fBshorewall\-nft start\fR; read by \fBshorewalld\fR as
the set-population allowlist.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PYTHONPATH
Standard Python module search path. Required when running from a
development checkout without a system install.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Compile error, verification failure, or runtime error.
.TP
.B 2
Argument parsing or usage error.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Start the firewall using the default config directory:
.RS
.nf
shorewall\-nft start
.fi
.RE
.PP
Debug a specific traffic flow in a netns:
.RS
.nf
shorewall\-nft debug /etc/shorewall46 \e
    \-\-netns fw \e
    \-\-trace 'ip saddr 192.168.1.100'
.fi
.RE
.PP
Merge dual\-stack config, then verify against iptables baseline:
.RS
.nf
shorewall\-nft merge\-config /etc/shorewall /etc/shorewall6
shorewall\-nft verify \-\-iptables /tmp/iptables\-save.txt
.fi
.RE
.PP
Block an address temporarily, then release it:
.RS
.nf
shorewall\-nft blacklist 198.51.100.5 \-t 2h
shorewall\-nft allow 198.51.100.5
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewalld (8),
.BR nft (8),
.BR iptables (8),
.BR ip-netns (8)

